qas.question: When did Estonia join the European Union's Nordic Battle Group?
What government institution did Estonia continue to show desire in joining?
What percentage of Estonia's foreign trade was held by Russia in 1992?
What percentage of Estonia exports are sent to Nordic countries?

context: In <a0_0>2005<a0_0/>, Estonia joined the European Union's Nordic Battle Group. It has also shown continued interest in joining <a1_0>the Nordic Council<a1_0/>. Whereas in 1992 Russia accounted for <a2_0>92%<a2_0/> of Estonia's international trade, today there is extensive economic interdependence between Estonia and its Nordic neighbours: three quarters of foreign investment in Estonia originates in the Nordic countries (principally Finland and Sweden), to which Estonia sends <a3_0>42%<a3_0/> of its exports (as compared to 6.5% going to Russia, 8.8% to Latvia, and 4.7% to Lithuania). On the other hand, the Estonian political system, its flat rate of income tax, and its non-welfare-state model distinguish it from the Nordic countries and their Nordic model, and indeed from many other European countries.
